                          	<p class="feature-content text-justify">

                          	Learning is more effective when simple learning content is enriched with relevant supplementary content from a variety of sources – illustrations, videos, practice questions, quizzes and more. Learning is further enhanced when such supplementary content is matched to individual learner preferences. But the human effort and cost of doing this for large number of learners across thousands of topics is a humongous task. And that is why we built the SunBird semantic engine, so you can provide an immersive learning experience to every learner cost effectively.</p>

<p class="feature-content text-justify">SunBird's Semantic Engine builds the taxonomy of concepts for any subject space, which could be thousands of concepts and the relationships among them – such as related concepts, pre-requisites and so on. It then extracts concepts covered in any piece of content and the pedagogic intent for each – whether the concept is introductory, explanatory, reference information etc.  Cross referencing this with the taxonomy for the subject areas, the engine is now able to index thousands of relevant content elements from public sources and well as private corporate repositories.</p>

<p class="feature-content text-justify">With the content index in place, for any given learning content SunBird can suggest pedagogically suitable additional content and even questions or exercises. Your content is now ready to adapt itself for various learner needs. And if you are not using the SunBird learning platform, you could still enrich all your existing content by using our APIs. Simple, right?</p>


